public int earliestBlooms(int[] plantTime, int[] growTime) {
    int n = plantTime.length;
    int[][] processTime = new int[n][2];
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        processTime[i][0] = plantTime[i];
        processTime[i][1] = growTime[i];
    }
    Arrays.sort(processTime, (a, b) -> a[0] - b[0]);

    int day = 0;
    int blooms = 0;
    for (int[] p : processTime) {
        day += p[0];
        blooms = Math.max(blooms, day + p[1]);
    }
    return blooms;
}
```

    1. Create a new list/array, `processTime`, containing pairs/tuples of (plantTime, growTime) for each seed.
2. Sort `processTime` in ascending order based on plantTime.
3. Iterate through the sorted `processTime` pairs/tuples. For each pair/tuple, increment the `day` counter by the plantTime, and compare the sum of `day` and growTime with the current `blooms` value. If the sum is greater, update `blooms` with the new value.
4. Return the final `blooms` value as the earliest day when all seeds have bloomed.
